xxl.core.relational.cursors
Class ResultSetMetaDataCursor

java.lang.Object
  xxl.core.cursors.AbstractCursor<Tuple>
      xxl.core.relational.cursors.ResultSetMetaDataCursor
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterator<Tuple>, Cursor<Tuple>, MetaDataCursor<Tuple,CompositeMetaData<Object,Object>>, MetaDataProvider<CompositeMetaData<Object,Object>>
public class ResultSetMetaDataCursor
extends AbstractCursor<Tuple>
implements MetaDataCursor<Tuple,CompositeMetaData<Object,Object>>

This class wraps a result set to a metadata cursor. ResultSet and MetaDataCursor are equivalent concepts. Both handle sets of objects with metadata. The different direction is done by the class MetaDataCursorResultSet.

createTuple

protected Function<? super ResultSet,? extends Tuple> createTuple
The function that maps a (row of the) result set to a tuple. The function gets a result set and maps the current row to a tuple. It is forbidden to call the next, update and similar methods.

Constructor Detail

ResultSetMetaDataCursor

public ResultSetMetaDataCursor(ResultSet resultSet,
                               Function<? super ResultSet,? extends Tuple> createTuple)
Constructs a Wrapper that wraps a result set into a metadata cursor. Therefore, a function can be passed that translates a row into an object.

Parameters:
resultSet - the result set that is wrapped into a metadata cursor.
createTuple - the function that maps a (row of the) result set to a tuple. The function gets a result set and maps the current row to a tuple. It is forbidden to call the next, update and similar methods of the result set!

ResultSetMetaDataCursor

public ResultSetMetaDataCursor(ResultSet resultSet)
Constructs a Wrapper that wraps a result set into a metadata cursor. The rows of the result set are represented by array-tuples.

Parameters:
resultSet - the result set that is wrapped into a metadata cursor.

remove

public void remove()
            throws WrappingRuntimeException
Removes from the underlying collection the last element returned by the cursor. This call does only work if the underlying result set supports the deleteRow-call of JDBC 2.0. This method can be called only once per call to next or peek. The behavior of a cursor is unspecified if the underlying result set is modified while the iteration is in progress in any way other than by calling this method.

Specified by:

reset

public void reset()
           throws WrappingRuntimeException
Resets the cursor to its initial state. So the caller is able to traverse the underlying collection again. The modifications, removes and updates concerning the underlying collection, are still persistent. This call does only work if the underlying result set supports the beforeFirst-call of JDBC 2.0.

update

public void update(Tuple tuple)
            throws WrappingRuntimeException
Replaces the object that was returned by the last call to next or peek. This operation must not be called after a call to hasNext. It should follow a call to next or peek. This method should be called only once per call to next or peek. The behavior is unspecified if the underlying result set is modified while the iteration is in progress in any way other than by calling this method. This call does only work if the underlying result set supports the updateObject-call of JDBC 2.0.

Specified by:
update in interface Cursor<Tuple>
Overrides:
update in class AbstractCursor<Tuple>
Parameters:
tuple - the object that replaces the object returned by the last call to next or peek.
Throws:
WrappingRuntimeException - if the underlying result set reports a SQLException.
